added.title: Hey Pizza!
added.description: Beast Boy and Cyborg try their best to slow the pizza delivery boy so they can get free pizza.

added.title: Tiger Philanthropist
added.description: Steven returns to the ring to continue his pro wrestling odyssey.

added.title: Greg the Babysitter
added.description: Steven learns the tale of how Greg came to work at the car wash.

added.title: Giant Woman
added.description: During a mission to the Sky Spire, Steven tries to convince Amethyst and Pearl to fuse together and become a giant woman.

added.title: Garnet's Universe
added.description: Steven imagines what Garnet does with her day.

added.title: Future Vision
added.description: Steven learns that Garnet can see into the future and becomes curious about the possible dangers that lurk around him.

added.title: The Egg
added.description: To impress the mother of Anais' playdate, Nicole forces her family to get classy. Nicole arranges a playdate for Anais with the son of a classy lady she met at the supermarket. She hopes that socializing with the right sort of people will help her children climb Elmore's social ladder. The Wattersons try to impress, but ultimately cannot help revealing their true natures. The grown-ups become convinced they want nothing more to do with each other, just as Anais and her playdate discover how much they have in common.

added.title: The Dream
added.description: When Gumball blames Darwin for kissing Penny in his dream it threatens to tear apart their friendship, the only place you can fix a dream problem is in the dream world.

added.title: The Debt
added.description: Gumball resolves to save Mr Robinson's life during Elmore's Senior Talent Show.

added.title: The End
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are convinced that the world will end in 24 hours.

added.title: The Dress
added.description: Gumball goes to school in a dress and becomes the darling of Elmore High.

added.title: Popularity Conquest
added.description: When Mao Mao discovers that he is not as popular as Badgerclops and Adorabat, they decide to reinvent him as a kinder, cuddlier hero.

added.title: The Movie Theater Car
added.description: One-One is treated to the one-of-a-kind entertainment of the Movie Theater Car.

added.title: The Cross-Eyed Ducks Car
added.description: One-One shows off the resplendent majesty of The Cross-Eyed Ducks Car.

added.title: Things That Go Plunk
added.description: A shy, puny member of the Bad Crowd shows up at the Cloudseeker claiming he's been kicked out of Blusterland for being nice. The Bears, leery at first, take him in despite Grumpy's suspicions that he is in cahoots with Bluster. It appears Grumpy is right - but thanks to the Care Bears, the little guy turns into a good friend with the courage to thwart Bluster's latest scheme.

added.title: On the Trail of the Cloud Bouncer
added.description: When spores from a strange plant take over control of the Cloudseeker, Cheer and the team must risk losing the vehicle - their home away from home and their only way back to Care-A-Lot - in order to save the Whiffles' newly-planted valley.

added.title: Festival of Hearts
added.description: When two greedy gnomes steal Love-a-Lot's gift-making crystal heart, the Care Bears must get it back in time for the Festival of Hearts that they are holding for the Whiffles. In doing so, they have to teach the gnomes the meaning of caring.

added.title: Riffle the Whiffle
added.description: The Bears encounter a lost Whiffle whose only word is "Riffle." They have no idea who he is or where he came from. Dibble is tasked with looking out for him until they learn where he lives. At first delighted to have a new playmate, she grows frustrated when he seems only to want to get away. With the aid of the Bears, Dibble helps solve the mystery of who he is and where he belongs.

added.title: Planet X
added.description: When Rad returns to his home planet, he learns a shocking truth about alien society.

added.title: Gar Trains Punching Judy
added.description: With a big fight coming up, Punching Judy turns to KO and Gar to help her prepare.

added.title: OK A.U.!
added.description: An evil warlock takes our heroes to a strange alternate universe.

added.title: Rad's Alien Sickness
added.description: When our heroes are infected with a virus, Rad stubbornly refuses to back down.

added.title: Haunted Campfire
added.description: The campers must battle ghosts of their own creation after their scary stories mysteriously come true.

added.title: Food Chain
added.description: On a field trip to the Candy Kingdom Museum of Natural History, Finn and Jake learn about the Food chain by becoming the food chain!

added.title: Friends Forever
added.description: Ice King plots to form a perfect circle of confidants.

added.title: Late Night Good Morning With Uncle Grandpa
added.description: It's the Late Night Good Morning show with your host, Uncle Grandpa!

added.title: The Longest Weekend
added.description: Muscle Man has to make it through a week without contacting Starla.

added.title: Caveman
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to civilize a caveman so that Benson will let him stay at the park.

added.title: Uncle Dummy
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve try to convince Mr. Gus that his ventriloquist dummy is alive.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: Clarence for President
added.description: It's school election time at Aberdale Elementary, and Jeff is once again determined to become Class President. However like previous years, he's unsuccessful in connecting with other kid. That is until he sees a shoe-in puppet President, the lovable Clarence!

added.title: Fleas Help Me
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang help their K9 pal, Charlie Burgers, get rid of his flea infestation.

added.title: Eggscellent
added.description: Mordecai wants to win a hat for Rigby.

added.title: Truth
added.description: An old Plumber partner of Max's resurfaces with nefarious intentions and ends up stealing the dangerous Null Void Projector.

added.title: Framed
added.description: Kevin 11 is back and out for revenge. And with the ability to shape-shift into several of Ben's alien heroes, he's been framing Ben for his crimes.

added.title: Tough Luck
added.description: Gwen's Lucky Girl powers return when she buys a magical stone at a magic convention in Las Vegas. However, Hex is after the same stone, and after his niece breaks him out of prison, the two set off to retrieve the stone.

added.title: Pal.0
added.description: When the RV's talking computer system malfunctions, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must figure out a way to stop the rogue computer and restore life in the RV back to normal.

added.title: Infinite Vendetta Part 1
added.description: The Autobots and Decepticons are surprised by the return of their long-lost comrades, Jetfire and Skybyte.

added.title: Monkey Love
added.description: When Blossom makes a bad call, she becomes afraid to try again.

added.title: Infinite Vendetta Part 2
added.description: Starscream gives Jetfire and Skybyte Spark Armor to escalate their feud and distract everyone from his machinations.

added.title: Find Your Bliss
added.description: When Bubbles blames a string of accidents on her imaginary friend "Bliss," her sisters begin to think she's lost her mind.

added.title: Blisster Sister
added.description: The Girls hang out with their new big sister Bliss, who gets a taste of fighting bad guys as part of the Powerpuff Girls.

added.title: Blisstersweet Symphony
added.description: When Him absorbs Bliss and her powers, the Girls must work together to rescue their sister and save Townsville from destruction.

added.title: The Trouble With Bubbles
added.description: When Bubbles is overworked, she uses her coding skills to come up with a new solution.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 2
added.description: Ben and Rook discover an underground city beneath Bellwood populated with aliens! But who is terrorizing them? (Introducing Nemetrix alien BugLizard, & Ben alien Shocksquatch, Psyphon, Fistina, Bubblehelmet, Liam.)

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: Meat Your Maker
added.description: After Rigby causes the guys to get locked in a meat locker, he must get help from some hot dogs in order to get them out.

added.title: Evicted!
added.description: Marceline shows up and informs that the tree fort was once hers and she wants it back.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: Puddle Eyes
added.description: A nap in mud seals Clarence's eyes and leaves him sightless, potentially dooming his team's chances in the school's ill-conceived "Vision Bee."

added.title: Dream Boat
added.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

added.title: Malefactor
added.description: Khyber and his dog attacks Ben and Rook while they're at the "Olde Bellwood Days" festival, but does the hunter have other plans? (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Hypnotick.)

added.title: Store 23
added.description: While out looking for the elusive 23rd Mr. Smoothy's store with Blukic and Driba, Ben meets an alternate version of himself. (Guest-starring Aziz Ansari as Ben 23.)

added.title: Freak City
added.description: A magical man turns Finn into a foot. They meet others who have been similarly wronged and must work together.

added.title: Finn Meets His Hero
added.description: Finn meets his adventuring role model, only to learn he's become a wuss in his old age.

added.title: New Kid
added.description: Uncle Grandpa gives a kid a haircut that is too cool for school.

added.title: Bakugan: Best Brawl Ever - Drago vs. Hyrdorous
added.description: Dan remembers one of his favorite brawls ever, with Drago and Hydorous battling it out for the win.

added.title: Bakugan: Best Brawl Ever - Fade Ninja vs. the Boxers
added.description: Shun Kazami recalls one of his intensive brawls, where his Bakugan Fade Ninja goes up against Marco's Black Boxer and White Boxer.

added.title: Bakugan: Best Brawl Ever - Trox vs. Krakelios
added.description: Wynton relives his Best Brawl Ever with Ventus Trox against Strata's Aquos Bakugan Krakelios.

added.title: Bakugan: Best Brawl Ever - Cubbo vs. Mantanoid
added.description: Lia flashes back to one of her most unique brawls with the cute but prickly Cubbo facing off against Aay's Mantanoid Bakugan.

added.title: Drago Maximus vs Titan Nillious
added.description: It is an intensive showdown when Dan's favorite rival Magnus gives Drago good reason to fear the might of Nillious in brawl to end all brawls.

added.title: Bakugan: Best Brawl Ever - Kelion vs. Skorporos
added.description: Dan has triple the fun when his Bakugan beast Kelion takes on three Skorporos in one of his best battles ever!

added.title: Bakugan: Best Brawl Ever - Lupitheon vs. Pandox
added.description: Wynton highlights why it takes a good brawler and Bakugan to win a battle, in this face off between Lupitheon and Pandoxx.

added.title: Bakugan: Best Brawl Ever - Howlkor vs. Artulean
added.description: Lighting's Bakugan go head to head to see who's the better brawler.

added.title: Bakugan: Beyond the Brawl - Too Many Ninjas
added.description: A game of "Tag" becomes infuriating for Hydorous when Fade Ninja bends the rules Bakugan-style to win.

added.title: This Man, This Man Man!
added.description: When Guts Man goes on a ravenous rampage across the city, Mega Man must turn to an unlikely ally, Man Man, a bumbling DIY human analog to our hero.

added.title: A Guilded Cage
added.description: Mega Man must stop Namagem and an army of hypnotized Good Guild bots from breaking into Dr. Light's lab.

added.title: To Air Is Robot
added.description: Air Man stakes a claim on the skies above Silicon City, threatening anything that trespasses on his airspace.

added.title: Watt's Happening?!
added.description: When Elec Man derails the school play by hijacking Silicon Central's power, Aki/Mega Man must use what he has learned onstage to defeat his supercharged foe.

added.title: Chill Out, Bruh
added.description: Aki and Suna take a rehabilitated Ice Man out for a day in the city, but things take a turn for the worse as he misinterprets their cues and turns a game of hover hockey into a literal freeze out!

added.title: Campeon del Cuadro
added.description: iCraig promete hacer que el juego de Cuatro Cuadros vuelva a ser divertido cuando desafía a su jugador más experto!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Portal hacia Helen
added.description: Craig hace una conexión a larga distancia con un niño que ama el Arroyo tanto como él.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El ultimo nino en el Arroyo
added.description: Por una terrible maldición, Craig se convierte en el único niño del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: A escalar
added.description: iEl teléfono de Craig se atasca en el Monte Sicomoro, el árbol más alto del Arroyo!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Don Pellizco
added.description: JP lleva a sus amigos de viaje para encontrar el cangrejo de río más grande del Arroyo.
